Task 4
Setup and Use a Firewall on Windows
This task shows basic firewall setup using **Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security**.
##Tools Used
Windows 10, operating system where the firewall was configured.
Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security, GUI tool to create and manage inbound and outbound rules.
Command Prompt (CMD), used to view firewall rules and test connectivity on specific ports.
Telnet Client, tested blocking of Telnet, Port 23.
Netstat Utility, verified allowed ports, for example, SSH on Port 22.
##Steps Performed
- Opened Windows Firewall (`wf.msc`).
- Listed existing inbound rules.
- Created a rule to **block Telnet (port 23)**.
- Created a rule to **allow SSH (port 22)**.
- Verified rules using Command Prompt.
- Removed the test block rule.
##Outcome
- Learned how to add, verify, and remove firewall rules.
- Understood inbound and outbound filtering and the importance of blocking insecure ports.

